753
01:07:48,154 --> 01:07:55,398
[SPEAKER_13]: Are there other changes to items two or three before we move to the next slide?

754
01:07:57,399 --> 01:07:57,659
[SPEAKER_13]: Ken?

755
01:07:57,679 --> 01:08:05,244
[SPEAKER_14]: I just wanted to add in that there's really no harm in having some extra categories in there.

756
01:08:06,224 --> 01:08:10,207
[SPEAKER_14]: These categories are not going to add up to a number that makes us do something.

757
01:08:11,123 --> 01:08:14,886
[SPEAKER_14]: It's comparative to other options.

758
01:08:15,046 --> 01:08:21,292
[SPEAKER_14]: So individual people may put more interest or weight on an individual.

759
01:08:21,392 --> 01:08:29,399
[SPEAKER_14]: Like somebody may want, I want to maximize PV, and that's the most important thing to me in that scenario.

760
01:08:29,799 --> 01:08:35,524
[SPEAKER_14]: So you could, you know, one person may want to strike certain alternatives.

761
01:08:35,904 --> 01:08:38,105
[SPEAKER_14]: because that's more important than to the other.

762
01:08:38,625 --> 01:08:47,127
[SPEAKER_14]: It's not that a total number is a, you know, we can't choose an option if it has the lowest total number or the highest total number.

763
01:08:47,607 --> 01:08:51,208
[SPEAKER_14]: It's just a number that adds up what those options are.

764
01:08:51,568 --> 01:08:54,649
[SPEAKER_14]: And different sections are gonna mean different things to different people.

765
01:08:55,129 --> 01:09:01,571
[SPEAKER_14]: You know, so you may, parking is the most important thing to you, or the football field practices, and you're gonna personally,

766
01:09:02,031 --> 01:09:09,537
[SPEAKER_14]: look at those when you compare the options and choose different options that you feel should stay in for the PSR based on that compared to other people.

767
01:09:09,557 --> 01:09:12,159
[SPEAKER_13]: Thanks, Ken.

768
01:09:12,179 --> 01:09:18,084
[SPEAKER_13]: Are there any other motions about category two or three?

769
01:09:18,104 --> 01:09:19,805
[SPEAKER_03]: Okay.

