01:33:53,973 --> 01:33:54,193
[SPEAKER_00]: Yes.

1181
01:33:54,553 --> 01:34:01,016
[SPEAKER_00]: I absolutely don't have any issue with the intent of what was just passed in that motion.

1182
01:34:01,036 --> 01:34:06,879
[SPEAKER_00]: I just have absolutely no idea how we will measure it in the 29 options.

1183
01:34:08,339 --> 01:34:09,940
[SPEAKER_00]: So I don't think we need to

1184
01:34:10,553 --> 01:34:18,115
[SPEAKER_00]: answer that today, but I think somebody needs to be thinking about, you know, how does something, how is something a zero versus a five?

1185
01:34:18,155 --> 01:34:29,458
[SPEAKER_00]: I mean, a fully blown, just do the code upgrade will not increase the square footage one inch, and therefore that would be a five.

1186
01:34:31,357 --> 01:34:36,278
[SPEAKER_00]: all the other options that are going to increase the space that we use are going to be the worst options.

1187
01:34:36,818 --> 01:34:44,000
[SPEAKER_00]: I just don't understand how we're from the 29 options we have today that are at the level of detail we have.

1188
01:34:44,360 --> 01:34:46,340
[SPEAKER_00]: We don't know what the building is going to look like at all.

1189
01:34:46,360 --> 01:34:51,241
[SPEAKER_00]: How are we going to know what's a zero and what's a five?

1190
01:34:51,521 --> 01:34:59,843
[SPEAKER_13]: Paul, I think my understanding or intention when I voted yes was that the project team was going to

1191
01:35:01,779 --> 01:35:07,624
[SPEAKER_13]: come up with something that was measurable that got to that point.

1192
01:35:07,705 --> 01:35:15,111
[SPEAKER_13]: So what we were asking was that the project team add something that reflects responsible stewardship.

1193
01:35:15,191 --> 01:35:18,875
[SPEAKER_13]: So I think we'll wait to see what they come up with.

1194
01:35:19,395 --> 01:35:21,878
[SPEAKER_00]: But stewardship is a pretty loaded word.

1195
01:35:22,378 --> 01:35:27,203
[SPEAKER_00]: I mean, there are probably plenty of people who think the proper stewardship of a lot of these lands that used to be native lands

1196
01:35:28,293 --> 01:35:29,834
[SPEAKER_00]: is to return them to nature.

1197
01:35:30,314 --> 01:35:33,076
[SPEAKER_00]: Like that's the proper, that's stewardship.

1198
01:35:33,996 --> 01:35:44,381
[SPEAKER_00]: So I don't know what stewardship means and how does the project team decide what that, stewardship to me would mean the smallest amount of land used and returning the rest of it to nature.

1199
01:35:45,422 --> 01:35:46,923
[SPEAKER_00]: That's what stewardship to me would mean.

1200
01:35:47,943 --> 01:35:50,264
[SPEAKER_00]: That means we wouldn't bring any fields over.

1201
01:35:50,465 --> 01:35:53,506
[SPEAKER_00]: We wouldn't have any parking, no parking.

1202
01:35:53,746 --> 01:35:56,928
[SPEAKER_00]: If you want to talk about stewardship of the land, no parking.

1203
01:35:57,622 --> 01:35:59,023
[SPEAKER_00]: make people bike and walk.

1204
01:35:59,483 --> 01:36:15,974
[SPEAKER_00]: So I don't know, I have no idea what is intended by stewardship because it seems like an incredibly, it's based on a whole lot about morality and ethics and, you know, your understanding of history.

1205
01:36:15,994 --> 01:36:18,435
[SPEAKER_00]: I don't know what this means.

1206
01:36:18,535 --> 01:36:20,576
[SPEAKER_00]: I'm also not a voting member, so I'll stop talking.

1207
01:36:23,623 --> 01:36:34,826
[SPEAKER_13]: You know, once the project team has a chance to digest that, if they need to come back to us and clarify how they're evaluating that or ranking it, we can talk about that in our next meeting on the 23rd.

1208
01:36:39,628 --> 01:36:40,088
[SPEAKER_13]: Okay.

1209
01:36:47,390 --> 01:36:50,411
[SPEAKER_13]: Is there anything else about items 7 through 10?

1210
01:36:52,760 --> 01:36:53,782
[SPEAKER_13]: that we would like to change.

