1264
01:39:41,509 --> 01:39:46,330
[SPEAKER_13]: Are there any additional changes to items 7 through 10?

1265
01:39:49,797 --> 01:39:55,100
[SPEAKER_06]: I would like to have a discussion to see if there's any support for breaking up some of these in 10.

1266
01:39:56,241 --> 01:40:01,205
[SPEAKER_06]: I feel like there's a particular value to facilitating community use and access to the pool.

1267
01:40:01,585 --> 01:40:04,668
[SPEAKER_06]: And I think that's separate from community access and use of the gym.

1268
01:40:05,288 --> 01:40:11,753
[SPEAKER_06]: And it's separate for the fitness spaces, which include the gymnastics area and the baseball batting cages.

1269
01:40:12,293 --> 01:40:13,574
[SPEAKER_06]: I feel like those are all separate things.

1270
01:40:15,938 --> 01:40:31,974
[SPEAKER_06]: You know, before I make another motion that gets killed, I just want to know if anybody else thinks that there's value in breaking these up because they really do speak to different parts of the community and should probably have their own categories.

1271
01:40:33,716 --> 01:40:35,398
[SPEAKER_13]: Are you thinking about splitting up 10.2, 10.3?

1272
01:40:41,986 --> 01:40:58,294
[SPEAKER_06]: So definitely 10.2 and potentially 10.3, because I think personally, it'd be great if the auditorium was like the one they had at Somerville, where you can hold shows without disrupting or having to access the school.

1273
01:40:59,915 --> 01:41:01,536
[SPEAKER_06]: I don't know what the support spaces are.

1274
01:41:01,556 --> 01:41:03,477
[SPEAKER_06]: I don't know what that is.

1275
01:41:03,797 --> 01:41:08,980
[SPEAKER_06]: So I wouldn't necessarily move to break up 10.3, because again, I don't know what the support spaces are.

1276
01:41:09,520 --> 01:41:12,321
[SPEAKER_06]: But I would definitely move to break up 10.2.

1277
01:41:16,964 --> 01:41:24,747
[SPEAKER_13]: Luke, I will just say from myself, I think 10.2 and 10.3 deserve that separate intention.

1278
01:41:24,767 --> 01:41:28,369
[SPEAKER_13]: And I'd be happy to second your motion if you want to make it.

1279
01:41:28,389 --> 01:41:35,532
[SPEAKER_06]: I will make that motion, but can someone just tell me what the support spaces are?

1280
01:41:37,625 --> 01:41:45,411
[SPEAKER_01]: So I think the intent is that the support spaces are those spaces that allow the auditorium to sort of function as an autonomous space.

1281
01:41:45,471 --> 01:41:53,417
[SPEAKER_01]: So say like the toilet rooms, the lobby space, things that are required for the auditorium to ticket window potentially.

1282
01:41:54,097 --> 01:41:58,360
[SPEAKER_01]: So I think 10.3 could probably get by without being split apart.

1283
01:41:59,121 --> 01:41:59,961
[SPEAKER_01]: Understand that 10.2

1284
01:42:01,173 --> 01:42:03,415
[SPEAKER_01]: the intent there, and I think that would add something.

1285
01:42:04,055 --> 01:42:05,696
[SPEAKER_01]: I will just caveat it as well.

1286
01:42:05,757 --> 01:42:17,926
[SPEAKER_01]: It goes back to this notion of we're splitting things up, and if everything is weighted equally, we're essentially going to be giving additional support to anything besides the code repair option, right?

1287
01:42:17,946 --> 01:42:27,113
[SPEAKER_01]: Because I think at the level of detail of where we are right now, we have to probably make an assumption that all of the designs can achieve

1288
01:42:27,730 --> 01:42:32,372
[SPEAKER_01]: um, having an improved level of access, um, to say the pool, the gym and the fitness spaces.

1289
01:42:33,232 --> 01:42:38,154
[SPEAKER_01]: Um, just cause we, we don't know, we haven't got to the detail level of laying out all those spaces again.

1290
01:42:38,194 --> 01:42:41,975
[SPEAKER_01]: I think it sort of recurring theme that we've had, um, as we've gone through here.

1291
01:42:42,015 --> 01:42:48,958
[SPEAKER_01]: So it will increase sort of those positives, um, that go towards, um, in addition renovation or a new construction option.

1292
01:42:49,058 --> 01:42:50,618
[SPEAKER_01]: And I don't think that's necessarily a bad thing.

1293
01:42:50,658 --> 01:42:55,240
[SPEAKER_01]: I just wanted to point out, um, sort of that's the effect of, um, splitting up some of these things.

1294
01:42:56,607 --> 01:42:57,648
[SPEAKER_13]: Um, Paul Malone.

1295
01:43:01,371 --> 01:43:06,455
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah, so I absolutely agree that 10.3, which is the auditorium.

1296
01:43:07,756 --> 01:43:08,597
[SPEAKER_16]: Needs, uh.

1297
01:43:09,878 --> 01:43:15,242
[SPEAKER_16]: Either an additional bullet or descriptive language that the auditorium spaces.

1298
01:43:16,403 --> 01:43:17,744
[SPEAKER_16]: Ideally could be used by

1299
01:43:23,370 --> 01:43:34,172
[SPEAKER_16]: separation from the educational and communal school spaces because I've been in the school where they've tried to do that and it's a nightmare.

1300
01:43:35,032 --> 01:43:45,634
[SPEAKER_16]: And in a lot of ways, even what you would think as sort of backstage and offstage spaces need to be used by outside artists or presenters or companies or contractors.

1301
01:43:45,874 --> 01:43:52,095
[SPEAKER_16]: And so it's not even as cut and dried as the traditional sort of front of house, back of house, box office,

1302
01:43:53,647 --> 01:43:57,390
[SPEAKER_16]: So I would definitely support adding a separate line.

1303
01:43:57,570 --> 01:44:17,102
[SPEAKER_16]: I do also think that those same struggles would happen with access to pool, gym, media center, any of those other places where you're just one doorway or one hallway or one bathroom away from suddenly being inside what is a student space or a classroom space.

1304
01:44:18,633 --> 01:44:38,141
[SPEAKER_16]: The other option I would just put out is maybe to save time, we just add like a 10.5, saying that we wanna measure if community uses can be separated and operate independently without using common or educational spaces.

1305
01:44:38,341 --> 01:44:40,802
[SPEAKER_16]: And then that might cover it enough for what we need to do.

1306
01:44:42,723 --> 01:44:46,505
[SPEAKER_13]: I'm gonna take a couple more comments and we can like come back to a motion.

1307
01:44:48,317 --> 01:44:49,498
[SPEAKER_14]: That was really a question for Matt.

1308
01:44:49,678 --> 01:44:56,462
[SPEAKER_14]: Shouldn't we expect as a standard design element that public and private spaces, except in the code option, will be separated?

1309
01:44:57,383 --> 01:45:05,468
[SPEAKER_14]: And we really wouldn't have this kind of level of information to know for sure because we haven't done adjacencies and all that in the design process yet.

1310
01:45:07,018 --> 01:45:12,582
[SPEAKER_01]: So yeah, Ken, I think that's you probably stated it better than I did in terms as I was trying to explain the differences there.

1311
01:45:13,062 --> 01:45:29,775
[SPEAKER_01]: And so it's a fine line, right, because we did choose to sort of suggest these four options or four criteria, which again are probably going to be similar at this level of detail that we have now for ad reno or new construction options versus the code repair.

1312
01:45:30,415 --> 01:45:33,777
[SPEAKER_01]: felt it was important to at least identify these.

1313
01:45:33,857 --> 01:45:45,622
[SPEAKER_01]: And I think the word access that's in there is really the thing that was intended to talk to the notion of separating out the access and use of those spaces from the rest of it.

1314
01:45:46,523 --> 01:45:51,345
[SPEAKER_01]: So we could potentially clarify that as well if that was of concern, sounds like it is.

1315
01:45:51,365 --> 01:45:55,087
[SPEAKER_13]: Thank you.

1316
01:45:55,127 --> 01:45:55,587
[SPEAKER_13]: Dr. Pelosi?

1317
01:45:58,048 --> 01:46:12,131
[SPEAKER_08]: I just wanted to call out where we're here on the community part, because some of our CTE programs to Matt and Ken's point too are also community facing, but we also use our buildings as community spaces.

1318
01:46:12,211 --> 01:46:15,511
[SPEAKER_08]: So we have the ECC that should probably be reflected here.

1319
01:46:16,592 --> 01:46:21,653
[SPEAKER_08]: Right now, Medford High School does contain a municipal daycare and the Medford Family Network.

1320
01:46:24,348 --> 01:46:35,057
[SPEAKER_08]: Those are community assets that need to be on here as well as Medford High School also houses our Welcome Center, our Parent Information Center.

1321
01:46:35,137 --> 01:46:40,382
[SPEAKER_08]: That's also part of our educational plan and should probably be reflected in here as well.

1322
01:46:46,188 --> 01:46:54,831
[SPEAKER_08]: I agree with separating 10.2 and 10.3, but I think we also have to add the Early Childhood Center and our Welcome Center.

1323
01:46:58,172 --> 01:47:01,093
[SPEAKER_06]: Well, Dr. Galussi, if you second mine, I'll second yours.

1324
01:47:02,754 --> 01:47:04,294
[SPEAKER_13]: How about that?

1325
01:47:04,314 --> 01:47:04,494
[SPEAKER_06]: Done.

1326
01:47:04,554 --> 01:47:04,834
[SPEAKER_06]: All right.

1327
01:47:04,875 --> 01:47:06,975
[SPEAKER_06]: So I'll make a motion to split up 10.2.

1328
